4.10.	We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to direct:
The concerned implementing offices to expedite the implementation of the PPAs to utilize the fund transfers within the prescribed period, and observe strictly the parameters set in the Memorandum of Agreement;
The OIC – Municipal Accountant to ensure prompt liquidation of fund transfers from NGAs upon completion of funded PPAs, and record the same in the books accordingly;
The OIC – Municipal Accountant to exhaust efforts in retrieving the supporting documents and expediting the return of the unexpended balances to the Source Agencies;
The OIC – Municipal Accountant to send confirmation letters to the Source Agencies to validate the balance per books of the prior years’ unutilized fund transfers; and
The Acting Municipal Treasurer to coordinate with the concerned implementing offices upon receipt of fund transfers from various NGAs for the timely implementation by the said offices of the PPAs.

7.11. 	We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to:
Direct the GSO Head to prepare the request for relief from accountability and its supporting documents, and submit the same to the COA Director as soon as possible to relieve him and the Municipality from the liability for the damaged property;
Require the GSO Head to determine the recoverable service amount of the fire-damaged Residual Containment Area so that the appropriate impairment loss, if any, will be recognized in the books of accounts;
Instruct the OIC – Municipal Accountant to record the impairment loss, if any, on the damaged asset and provide the adjusted depreciation allowance and necessary accounting disclosures following IPSAS 21; and
Direct the concerned personnel to verify if there is any MOA that supports the transfer of the Rainwater-Harvesting Facility, and get a copy thereof from the Iloilo Provincial Government for accounting and documentary purposes.
